>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1577.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/miscpics/couple.jpg height=200 width=100.gif></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Racial Hatred...  </span><hr size=1> Personally, I think that taking the very scanty and shallow framework SOE gave us for our races, and understanding it, and creating some interesting and original RP within that framework, is MUCH more of a challenge than just throwing it all aside and deciding 'hey I'm a happy good dark elf and I'll do whatever I want'.  For one thing, working within the guidelines allows a significant number of us to work in the same direction, which creates a true community RP feeling - something that's not possible if we all decide to make up whatever the heck we want to do.  But mainly, I feel it's a greater test of our skills and originality, to be original and interesting while still limiting oneself to the racial guidelines.<br>
<br>
That said, I have great respect for someone like Cronadan, who has learned the dark elf culture VERY well, and THEN decided to rebel against it, and has put a hell of a lot of work into doing so - I shudder to think how many hours he spent doing faction quests to convince the light races to trust him.  I have very little respect for a_necromancer_01 who wakes up one morning in Neriak and decides to giggle and hand out rat kebabs to passing paladins for no apparent reason, with no story to explain it and no faction work or similar effort to back up the persona.  And I consider this the greatest success of Zildrax and the Skathris Ven'Sho - they learned about the Iksar culture, and built their RP society on that framework, which has been elaborated and enhanced by all of them, resulting in an amazing benefit to our community here.  How terrible it would have been for all of us if the Skathris had never existed, and Iksar went around randomly deciding they would be 'good' today.<br>
<br>
My 2cp, flame away if you must, but I stand by it. <p><table border=0><tr><td width=20%><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif" height=120 width=120></td><td><FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC" SIZE="2">
